<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>{{ title }}</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
    <p>Your consumer and access keys have been submitted successfully. <strong>Note: they are not stored on this server.</strong></p>
    <hr>
    <div>
        {{ keys }}
    </div>
    <hr>
    <br>
        <p>
            You may visit the url {{ userTweetUrl }}/<strong>[twitteruser]</strong>/<strong>[numberOfTweets]</strong> to display tweets.
            Where <strong>[twitteruser]</strong> is the twitter user name and <strong>[numberOfTweets]</strong> is the number of tweets to display for the given username.
            <br>
            To return tweets in JSON form you can use the query parameter ?out=json like so: {{ userTweetUrl }}/<strong>[twitteruser]</strong>/<strong>[numberOfTweets]</strong>?out=json.
        </p>
        <p>
            For example, the URL for the last 15 tweets for the user <a href="https://twitter.com/bbcweather">@bbcweather</a> would be <a href="{{ userTweetUrl }}/bbcweather/15/">{{ userTweetUrl }}/bbcweather/15/</a>.
            <br>
            And for json form of the same example the URL would be: <a href="https://twitter.com/bbcweather">@bbcweather</a> would be <a href="{{ userTweetUrl }}/bbcweather/15?out=json">{{ userTweetUrl }}/bbcweather/15?out=json</a>.
        </p>
  </body>
</html>